PART 1: DOWNLOADING THE TOOL:
# Open your terminal (Linux/macOS) or Command Prompt (Windows)

# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/hebint.git

# 2. Enter the folder
cd hebint

# 3. Look at what's inside
ls -la  # Linux/macOS
# or
dir     # Windows

Option 2: Download as ZIP:
# 1. Go to the GitHub page in your browser
https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/hebint

# 2. Click the green "Code" button
# 3. Click "Download ZIP"
# 4. Extract the ZIP file to your desired location
#    - On Linux: right-click → Extract Here
#    - On Windows: right-click → Extract All

# 5. Open terminal and go to the extracted folder
cd ~/Downloads/hebint-main  # Linux/macOS
# or
cd C:\Users\YourName\Downloads\hebint-main  # Windows

 PART 2: SETTING UP THE TOOL:
python --version
# Should show Python 3.8 or higher

# If you have multiple Python versions, try:
python3 --version  # Linux/macOS
# or
py --version       # Windows


Step 2.2: Create Virtual Environment
For Linux/macOS:

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv

# Activate it
source venv/bin/activate

# You should see (venv) at the beginning of your terminal prompt

For Windows:

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Activate it
venv\Scripts\activate

# You should see (venv) at the beginning of your terminal prompt

Step 2.3: Install Dependencies:
# Make sure your virtual environment is activated (you see (venv))
pip install -r requirements.txt

# This installs:
# - requests (for web requests)
# - colorama (for colored output)
# - tqdm (for progress bars)

step 2.4: Verify Installation:
# Check that all packages installed
pip list

# You should see:
# requests   x.x.x
# colorama   x.x.x
# tqdm       x.x.x

Step 3.1: Basic Run:
# Make sure you're in the hebint folder
pwd  # Should show .../hebint

# Make sure virtual environment is activated (you see (venv))

# Run the tool
python modules/hebint_username.py

Step 3.2: Using the Launcher Script (Linux/macOS):
# Make the launcher executable
chmod +x hebint

# Run it
./hebint

Step 3.3: What You'll See:
👤 Advanced Username Module Ready!
✅ Loaded 72 platforms
Enter username to search: 

 MAKING IT A GLOBAL COMMAND:
# Method 1: Create an alias (easiest)
echo "alias hebint='cd ~/path/to/hebint && source venv/bin/activate && python modules/hebint_username.py'" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

# Now use from anywhere
hebint

If you get "ModuleNotFoundError":
pip install -r requirements.txt --upgrade

If virtual environment won't activate:
# Recreate it
deactivate  # if partially activated
rm -rf venv  # Linux/macOS
# or
rmdir /s venv  # Windows

python3 -m venv venv  # Linux/macOS
# or
python -m venv venv   # Windows

source venv/bin/activate  # Linux/macOS
# or
venv\Scripts\activate     # Windows

pip install -r requirements.txt

If you get "Permission denied":
chmod +x modules/hebint_username.py
chmod +x hebint

If you can't find the data folder:
# It's created automatically when you first run the tool
# If it doesn't exist, create it manually:
mkdir -p data

